casebody.data:
Jeffrey J. DAVIS, Appellant
v.
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellee No. 23 MAP 2018 Supreme Court of Pennsylvania. September 20, 2018

ORDER

PER CURIAM

AND NOW , this 20 th day of September, 2018, as Appellant failed to file exceptions to the April 6, 2018 order in the Commonwealth Court, the Notice of Appeal is quashed. See Pa.R.A.P. 1571(i) ; Commonwealth v. After Six, Inc. , 489 Pa. 69 , 413 A.2d 1017 , 1022-23 (Pa. 1980) (explaining that exceptions are required to be filed with the Commonwealth Court to preserve issues for an appeal to this Court as concerns review of a determination of the Board of Finance and Revenue).
